  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNHCR efforts in relation to the crisis in Syria, 2015</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNHCR is both responsible for the regional refugee assistance and the leading organisation in distributing non-food items and accommodating the many internally displaced people in Syria. More than 3.8 mio. Syrians are registred as refugees in the region - this is an increase on 1 mio. people since the summer of 2014. As the governments of the neighbouring countries limit the possibilities of Syrians for seeking refuge and accessing public benefits, the role of UNHCR grows increasingly important. UNHCR works to ensure the protection of refugees and help the neighbouring countries handle the influx of refugees. UNHCR has appealed for 1,35 billion USD to fund the regional refugee response in 2015.</narrative>
  </description>
